<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R2-043" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Multi-Document Selector in SprkChatContextSelector</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>frontend, fluent-ui</tags>
    <estimated-effort>medium</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies SprkChatContextSelector.tsx to support multi-select document state. Frontend and fluent-ui tags, .tsx modification. The additionalDocumentIds prop already exists but the multi-select UI and add/remove operations are R2 work.</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[006]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend `SprkChatContextSelector` to allow selecting multiple documents from the AnalysisWorkspace file list for multi-document analysis. Use the existing `additionalDocumentIds` prop (already typed in R1) to hold the selected document IDs. Show a selected document count badge. Support adding and removing individual documents from the selection.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior full-stack developer</role>

  <goal>
    SprkChatContextSelector shows a document count badge (e.g., "+3 docs") when multiple documents are selected. Clicking the badge opens a panel or popover listing selected documents with remove buttons. An "Add documents" button opens a document picker from the AnalysisWorkspace file list. The additionalDocumentIds prop is populated and passed to the BFF with each message for multi-document context injection.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="Project specification — FR-12 multi-document analysis, 5+ documents, shared 30K token budget">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="Project AI context — multi-document context architecture">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="Component to extend — context selector with additionalDocumentIds prop">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChatContextSelector.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="Main component — passes additionalDocumentIds to BFF">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="ADR-021 — Fluent v9 Badge, Popover, Panel patterns">../.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    <file purpose="ADR-012 — shared component library, callback props pattern">../.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-12">additionalDocumentIds MUST be sent to the BFF with each message for multi-document context injection — existing prop in R1 was never populated</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Document count badge MUST use Fluent v9 Badge or CounterBadge component — no custom badge implementations</criterion>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Document selection panel/popover MUST use callback-based props for document addition — SprkChatContextSelector does not directly query Dataverse</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Token budget is shared across all selected documents (30K total, not 30K per document) — UI should communicate multi-document sharing but enforcement is BFF-side</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChatContextSelector.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/types.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>Fluent v9 CounterBadge: import CounterBadge from @fluentui/react-components — shows numeric count, color="brand", size="small"</pattern>
      <pattern>Document picker integration: AnalysisWorkspace sends selected document IDs via SprkChatBridge or via a callback prop onAddDocuments(ids: string[]) — coordinate with BroadcastChannel events in task R2-051</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R1 typed the `additionalDocumentIds?: string[]` prop on SprkChatContextSelector but never populated it. The AnalysisWorkspace code page has a file list (list of documents in the analysis) that can source document IDs for multi-document analysis. R2 wires these together so users can select multiple documents from the AnalysisWorkspace file list and include them all in the AI context window.

      The BFF document context injection service (R2-012) handles aggregating multiple documents within a shared 30K token budget. The frontend only needs to pass the selected IDs.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on R2-006 (Phase 1 deploy). Can run in parallel with R2-040, R2-041, R2-042, R2-044. Connects to BFF task R2-012 (multi-document aggregation) during Phase 4 integration.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read SprkChatContextSelector.tsx to understand the current context indicator layout, props interface, and how additionalDocumentIds is currently handled (or ignored)</step>
    <step order="1">Confirm additionalDocumentIds prop is defined in ISprkChatContextSelectorProps — if not, add it as string[]</step>
    <step order="2">Add selectedDocuments state to SprkChat.tsx: string[] array managed at the SprkChat level, passed as additionalDocumentIds to SprkChatContextSelector</step>
    <step order="3">Add a Fluent v9 CounterBadge to SprkChatContextSelector showing the count of additionalDocumentIds when > 0</step>
    <step order="4">Make the CounterBadge clickable: open a Fluent v9 Popover listing selected documents with filename and a remove (X) button for each</step>
    <step order="5">Add "Add documents" button in the popover/panel: clicking opens a document picker. For now, implement as a Fluent v9 Dialog with a list of available documents from a passed prop (onRequestDocuments callback)</step>
    <step order="6">Implement remove document: clicking X on a listed document calls onRemoveDocument(id) callback → SprkChat.tsx removes it from selectedDocuments state</step>
    <step order="7">Ensure additionalDocumentIds is included in the chat message payload sent to the BFF — update the message send logic in SprkChat.tsx to include selectedDocuments</step>
    <step order="8">Add a tooltip on the counter badge: "Multiple documents selected — 30K token budget shared" to communicate the shared budget</step>
    <step order="9">Run TypeScript compilation: cd src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components &amp;&amp; npx tsc --noEmit — verify 0 errors</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-043 status to completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>npm</tool>
    <tool>git</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <artifact type="code">SprkChatContextSelector.tsx — extended with CounterBadge, document list popover, add/remove document UX</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">SprkChat.tsx — updated with selectedDocuments state management and inclusion in message payload</artifact>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">When additionalDocumentIds has 3 items, a badge showing "3" appears on the context selector</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Clicking the badge opens a popover listing selected documents with remove buttons</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Clicking remove on a document removes it from the selected list and decrements the badge count</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">additionalDocumentIds is included in the BFF message payload when documents are selected</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Badge uses Fluent v9 CounterBadge — not a custom div with a number</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TypeScript compilation passes with 0 errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
